properties.areaDesc: Waters from Point Reyes to Pigeon Point 10-60 NM
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued February 6 at 8:53PM PST until February 8 at 8:00PM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, northwest winds 15 to 25
kt with gusts up to 30 kt. For the Gale Watch, northwest winds
25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 45 kt and seas 9 to 14 feet at 14
seconds possible.

* WHERE...Waters from Point Reyes to Pigeon Point 10-60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 3 AM PST Saturday.
For the Gale Watch, from late Friday night through Saturday
evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM PST SATURDAY... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE FRIDAY NIGHT THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING
